comments: Professor Nita Slater is a staunch student advocate, highly qualified and the best of the best. This woman is so versatile she can teach any subject in nursing. And, with competence. Don\'t let her kindness fool you--she can be by the book, unyielding, but fair. Influential, admired and respected professor!

tag_professor: ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS (2)  Caring (1)  Gives good feedback (1)  Inspirational (1)
comments: Nita is a wonderful person and her lectures are very interesting. Her quizzes, however, are tough. It seems as if she pulls most of the questions out of thin air, not related to what was discussed in class. Or topics she barely mentions is a huge focus on the quiz, whereas some of the material you would think would be on the queiz is not.
